</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[680,771,1443,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis box="[680,771,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the following aspects: Caecum slightly curved upwards in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[282,369,1479,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis box="[282,369,1479,1503]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and straight in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[551,678,1479,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[551,678,1479,1503]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[685,775,1479,1504]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[685,775,1479,1504]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Saccus with short pointed apex (V-shaped) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[1301,1388,1479,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis box="[1301,1388,1479,1503]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and and strongly produced (Y-shaped) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[579,712,1515,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[579,712,1515,1539]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[720,806,1515,1540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">sp nov.</emphasis>
Valvae with three lobes in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[1122,1211,1515,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis box="[1122,1211,1515,1539]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only two in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[257,347,1551,1576]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,347,1551,1576]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Cucullus slightly shorter than valvula in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[809,896,1551,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis box="[809,896,1551,1575]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and longer than valvula in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[1209,1340,1551,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1209,1340,1551,1575]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1347,1436,1551,1576]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1347,1436,1551,1576]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
In female genitalia, we find the following differences between the species: signa absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[1168,1255,1587,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis box="[1168,1255,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while there are signa in the left ventral side in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[494,624,1623,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[494,624,1623,1647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[631,720,1623,1648]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[631,713,1623,1648]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Ductus seminalis arising from ductus bursae on the right side in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[151,238,1659,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis box="[151,238,1659,1683]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and on the left side in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[501,632,1659,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[501,632,1659,1683]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[638,728,1659,1684]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[638,728,1659,1684]" pageId="3" pageNumber="234">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
